<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>View all code problems in a file</b></p><p>There's no need to scroll down a file to see all detected problems: they are gathered in a dedicated <span class="control">Problems</span> tool window, where you can review them, apply a suggested fix, or fix them your own way.</p><p>Select <span class="control">View | Tool Windows | Problems</span> from the main menu or click the <span class="control">Inspections</span> widget in the top-right corner of the editor to open the tool window.</p><p class="image"><img src="images/problems-view.png" alt="Problems tool window" style="border: 1px solid #55555;" /></p></body></html>